			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We investigated the clinical significance of glucocorticoid receptor determination in 20 patients with systemic lupus erythematosus ( SLE ) who afterwards developed nephrotic syndrome . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Glucocorticoid receptor concentrations in mononuclear leukocytes ( MNL ) in these patients were comparable with those in both other patients with SLE and healthy persons . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Improvement in urinary protein excretion and in disease activity , which was scored according to the SLE Disease Activity Index system of the University of Toronto , closely related to the glucocorticoid receptor concentrations in MNL isolated from the corresponding patients . <S>",
